Functional Overview – Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System

The Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System is designed to manage the complete employee lifecycle through structured workflows, automation, and centralized data management.

1. User Management Functionality
Create, update, and delete user accounts.
Role-based access control (Admin, HR, Manager, IT, Employee).
Secure login and authentication system.
Password reset and account recovery.
2. Employee Management
Add new employee records.
Update employee details (designation, department, contact info).
View employee profile and history.
Search and filter employee database.
3. Onboarding Functionality
Automated onboarding request creation.
Assignment of onboarding tasks (HR, IT, Manager).
Document upload and verification.
Email creation and system access setup.
Training and orientation scheduling.
Onboarding progress tracking dashboard.
4. Offboarding Functionality
Initiation of resignation or termination process.
Approval workflow (Manager → HR → Finance → IT).
Asset return tracking (laptop, ID card, access cards).
Deactivation of system accounts and access rights.
Final settlement processing.
Exit interview scheduling and feedback collection.
5. Document Management
Upload and store employee documents securely.
Categorization of documents (Offer letter, ID proof, certificates, exit documents).
Download and preview options.
Access control for sensitive documents.
6. Asset Management
Assign company assets to employees.
Track asset usage and status.
Manage asset return during offboarding.
Maintain asset history records.
7. Notification System
Automated email/SMS alerts for:
Pending onboarding tasks
Approval requests
Asset return reminders
Exit process updates
8. Reporting and Analytics
Generate employee reports.
Onboarding and offboarding status reports.
Department-wise employee statistics.
Asset utilization reports.
Export reports in PDF/Excel formats.
9. Workflow Automation
Task assignment based on roles.
Sequential approval process.
Automatic status updates (Pending → In Progress → Completed).
Reduction of manual intervention.
